<TITLE> Protesters block traffic in Tejgaon after death of student </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, May 9 (bdnews24.com)Protesters blocked the road through Tejgaon after a bus ran over and killed a student of Dhaka Polytechnic Institute, police said. Angry students took to the streets and started vandalising cars passing through the area, Tejgaon police sub-inspector Mohammad Solaiman told bdnews24.com. The student who died in the road crash was identified as Ashiqur Rahman, 22, a resident of the institute's Latif Hall. The students set a Himalaya Paribahan bus ablaze and smashed four others to protest the death of Ashiq. Firemen rushed to the scene and doused the fire. Abdul Mannan, assistant police commissioner for Tejgaon zone, said the violence started around 10pm. The protesters hurled brickbats at the police who were trying to bring the situation under control. Many were seen wielding sticks. bdnews2
